{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-template-js","path":"/react-testing-snippets","result":{"data":{"BlogPostByPath":{"html":"<p>Assumptions:</p>\n<p>Jest for a test runner and <code>@testing-library/react</code></p>\n<h2 id=\"render-a-component\" style=\"position:relative;\">Render a component<a href=\"#render-a-component\" aria-label=\"render a component permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<pre><code>import React from 'react'\nimport { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport Login from '../login'\n\ntest('should show login form', () => {\n  render(&#x3C;Login />)\n  const input = screen.getByLabelText('Username')\n  // Events and assertions...\n})\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"check-for-props--prop-changes\" style=\"position:relative;\">Check for props &#x26; prop changes<a href=\"#check-for-props--prop-changes\" aria-label=\"check for props  prop changes permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>rerender</p>\n<h2 id=\"check-if-class-exists\" style=\"position:relative;\">Check if class exists<a href=\"#check-if-class-exists\" aria-label=\"check if class exists permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<h2 id=\"debug\" style=\"position:relative;\">Debug<a href=\"#debug\" aria-label=\"debug permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<pre><code>import { screen } from '@testing-library/dom'\nimport NiceComponent from './nice-component'\n\n\ntest('renders', () => {\n  const {debug} = render(&#x3C;NiceComponent />)\n    debug()\n})\n\n// or\n\ndocument.body.innerHTML = `\n  &#x3C;button>test&#x3C;/button>\n  &#x3C;span>multi-test&#x3C;/span>\n  &#x3C;div>multi-test&#x3C;/div>\n`\n\n// debug document\nscreen.debug()\n// debug single element\nscreen.debug(screen.getByText('test'))\n// debug multiple elements\nscreen.debug(screen.getAllByText('multi-test'))\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"inputs\" style=\"position:relative;\">Inputs<a href=\"#inputs\" aria-label=\"inputs permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>label exists</li>\n<li>id matches</li>\n<li>input type</li>\n<li>placeholder</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"events\" style=\"position:relative;\">Events<a href=\"#events\" aria-label=\"events permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<h2 id=\"getby-vs-queryby\" style=\"position:relative;\"><code>getBy</code> vs <code>queryBy</code><a href=\"#getby-vs-queryby\" aria-label=\"getby vs queryby permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p><code>getBy</code> is what you should use by default.  It gives helpful error messages to help you fix broken tests.  It will return with an error.</p>\n<p><code>queryBy</code> is what to use when you are testing is something is <em>NOT</em> rendered.  It returns null if the element is not found.</p>\n<p>tl;dr use <code>getBy</code> unless you mean are testing something isn't rendered.</p>\n<h2 id=\"accessibility-testing\" style=\"position:relative;\">Accessibility testing<a href=\"#accessibility-testing\" aria-label=\"accessibility testing permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<h2 id=\"extending-expect\" style=\"position:relative;\">Extending expect<a href=\"#extending-expect\" aria-label=\"extending expect permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Jest gives you expect</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@testing-library/extend-expect</li>\n<li>@jest-axe/extend-expect</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-mock\" style=\"position:relative;\">How to Mock<a href=\"#how-to-mock\" aria-label=\"how to mock permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>your functions</li>\n<li>api calls / data fetching</li>\n<li>3rd party packages or components</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"June 11th, 2021","path":"/react-testing-snippets","title":"React Testing Snippets","summary":" // 160 max characters","topic":"Technology","featuredImageAlt":"A description of what is in the image (not a caption)","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3354037267080745,"src":"/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/52efb/example-image.jpg","srcSet":"/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/f5236/example-image.jpg 215w,\n/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/9865e/example-image.jpg 430w,\n/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/52efb/example-image.jpg 860w,\n/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/1ff5b/example-image.jpg 1290w,\n/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/96dc6/example-image.jpg 1720w,\n/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/0723f/example-image.jpg 2412w","sizes":"(max-width: 860px) 100vw, 860px"}}}}},"SocialImage":{"frontmatter":{"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":1200,"height":630,"src":"/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/0eab3/example-image.jpg","srcSet":"/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/0eab3/example-image.jpg 1x,\n/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/b04b1/example-image.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/871581bc375a18466ef5acaa332ea98e/b5cc9/example-image.jpg 2x"}}}}}},"pageContext":{}}}